    "Denoising is important in refining these images, ensuring a clearer representation of the atomic structure.",
    "It enhances the level of detail in the images beyond the inherent resolution of the microscope, achieving higher spatial resolution, which allows researchers to discern finer structural features and better characterize atomic arrangements.",
    "By reducing noise and enhancing resolution, the method ensures a more accurate and robust analysis of atomic structures, even in challenging imaging conditions with variations in sample thickness.",
    "To show the generalizability of pretrained models in our work, we use the TEMImageNet data and do experiments on denoising, noise & background removal, and super-resolution.",
    "We use the HRNet model and run the same experiments to compare the results of fine-tuning to those of training with random weight initialization."
